Among different climatic factors, average minimum monthly temperature (°C) (r = 0.672, P<0.05, df = 10;
Fig 3a) and average monthly rainfall (mm) (r = 0.820, P<0.01, df = 10;
Fig 3b) are significantly correlated with occurrence of A. fulica in India (Table 6). Most records of A. fulica were from altitudes ranging from 1-100m asl (62.45%; Fig 4). There were few records from above 1000m asl.
